With Python 3.9 or later installed, run the following commands to set up the project:

$ python -m venv venv  # Create a virtual environment
$ source ./venv/bin/activate  # Activate the virtual environment
(venv) $ pip install -r requirements.txt  # Install the requirements

-----
With the virtual environment activated, you can run your solution with:

(venv) $ python solution.py

-----
Print if the optimization does not converge

(venv) $ python solution.py --raise_failure True

-----
Change maximum number of iterations for optimization routine

(venv) $ python solution.py --maxiter 1000

-----
Filter to choose only non-negative bids

(venv) $ python solution.py --non_negative_bids True

-----
Risk tolerance tuning

(venv) $ python solution.py --tune_risk_tol True --risk_tol 100 1000 200 --risk_tune_size 0.3

-----
Change daily volume limit

(venv) $ python solution.py --daily_volume_limit 200

-----
Change risk tolerance 

(venv) $ python solution.py --risk_tol 700



